default&#xa0;defaultRecommendationsdefault&#xa0;
defaultThe independent retail sector in Northern Ireland is one of the most innovative, vibrant, varied and important - but it is also one of the most fragile. 
default&#xa0;
defaultLacking the critical mass and resources of the large multiples, 
defaultindependent traders can be more susceptible to economic changes. Of those we surveyed who tried to access finance in the last three years, 35% were unsuccessful. This is concer
defaultning. We need a banking system 
defaultwhich better understands small retailers. Our mem
defaultbers are a key driver of growth in Northern Ireland and efficient funding and support is vital to our sector in supporting economic recovery.
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultWe would 
defaultmake the following recommendations
default:
default&#xa0;
defaultNorthern Ireland Banking Forumdefault&#xa0;
defaultAs Banking regulations are not a devolved matter, we suggest that the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland establish and Chair a 
defaultNI Banking Forum
default. This would include representatives from the Banks, Business Organisations and Executive Ministers for Ente
defaultrprise and Finance.
default&#xa0;
defaultWe envisage this Forum to be a mechanism to promote good communication and indeed to resolve any issues such as we have identified in our survey. This Forum should meet at least twice a year.
default&#xa0;
defaultBranch Vacancy Strategydefault&#xa0;defaultBank b
defaultranch
defaultes are
default a
defaultn
default essential element in our High Streets and Town Centres, both in terms of generating footfall and service provision for local traders.
default All the banks need to ensure that 
defaultthere is 
defaultadequate consultation with local stakeholders in advance of any intended cl
defaultosures.
default&#xa0;
defaultWith the high volume of bank branch closures in Northern Ireland we need all banks to commit themselves to a target of alternative use of the empty buildings within three months of closure.
default&#xa0;
defaultAlternative use such a new retail store, pop up shop, or
default being used a communi
defaultty group will boost 
defaultthe 
defaultfootfall which the branch closure has reduced. 
default&#xa0;
defaultOverdrafts and Credit Cardsdefault&#xa0;
defaultAs evidenced in our survey B
defaultanks unilaterally changing the o
defaultverdrafts of our members is still a cause for concern. We recommend a tig
defaulthtening of regulations covering the conditions on Overdraft and Credit cards to ensure that small business customers are not negatively impacted by any 
defaultsuch 
defaultchanges.
default 
default&#xa0;
defaultWe would recommend that 
defaultthe 
defaultFinancial Conduct Authority examine this area as a matter of
default priority.
